---
description: Enforce minimal, request-scoped code changes
alwaysApply: true
---

# Minimal Changes First

- Only implement what the user explicitly requested.
- Do not broaden scope unless the user asks.
- Do not refactor unrelated files "while here."
- Do not rename/move files unless required for the requested task.
- Prefer surgical edits over large rewrites.

# Allowed Expansion

- Expand scope only when needed to fix a directly related compile/test/runtime break.
- If expansion affects unrelated modules, ask for confirmation first.

# Safe Editing Pattern

- Read before editing.
- Modify the smallest viable set of files.
- Keep public APIs stable unless the request requires breaking changes.
- If extra improvements are found, list them as optional follow-ups instead of applying directly.

# Example

```text
Request: "Fix subapp route registration bug"
Do: update subapp registration logic and adjacent type definitions if needed.
Don't: reformat whole project, migrate router architecture, or rename unrelated files.
```
